From a1b030cef5aecd3c3089e4b283202118c1f361df Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rainbaby <rainbaby@outlook.jp>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 20:21:43 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 01/14] Add MMT/TLV container parser

MMT (MPEG Media Transport, ISO/IEC 23008-1 / MPEG-H Part 1) is an IP-native
transport with no file format of its own; ARIB STD-B32 packetizes its MMTP
stream into TLV packets to form the stored container used by Japanese ISDB-S3
BS/CS 4K/8K broadcasting (the same MMTP transport also underlies ATSC 3.0,
A/331). Files commonly carry the informal extension .mmts.

The parser:
- synchronizes on TLV packets (free re-sync when a stream does not start on a
  sync byte);
- walks compressed-IP -> MMTP -> signaling, reassembling messages fragmented
  across MMTP packets (the MPT is, so without reassembly no streams appear);
- maps the MPT asset list to streams: hev1 -> HEVC video, mp4a -> AAC audio,
  stpp -> TTML text (subtitle vs superimpose);
- exposes the MH-EIT[p/f] present event as a Menu chapter (name, description,
  scheduled start, duration), as DVB/ARIB EPG is surfaced from MPEG-TS.

Signed-off-by: Rainbaby <rainbaby@outlook.jp>
